&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Subject Matter Expert (AI SME)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Washington, DC Metro Area&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Artificial Intelligence (AI) Subject Matter Expert (SME) to join our team of technologists. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of both classical machine learning methodologies and cutting-edge generative AI. You will be responsible for advising on the design, development, and deployment of sophisticated ML models on Google Cloud Platform (GCP). This role requires a strategic thinker with a passion for research and a desire to solve complex challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in classic machine learning methodologies, including but not limited to, regression, classification, clustering, and ensemble methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience with generative AI models and techniques, such as Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), and large language models (LLMs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated proficiency with Google Cloud Platform (GCP) and its suite of machine learning services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong programming skills in Python and familiarity with common ML libraries and frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we are looking for in a strong candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Google Professional Machine Learning Engineer certification is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background working with the United States Air Force or other Department of Defense entities is a significant plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong track record in research, evidenced by publications or contributions to research projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with MLOps principles and practices for the continuous delivery and automation of machine learning models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently and in a team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build scalable and efficient ML models using both classic and generative AI techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the go-to expert for all machine learning-related inquiries, providing guidance and mentorship to other team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise and guide teams on how to deploy sophisticated and scalable ML models and pipelines on Google Cloud Platform, leveraging services such as Vertex AI, BigQuery ML, and AI Platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth research to stay at the forefront of the rapidly evolving fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities for leveraging machine learning to drive innovation and solve critical business and operational problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the robustness, fairness, and ethical implications of all developed models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
